content.problemStatement:
The `toLowerCase()` method in Java converts **all characters in a string to lowercase**. This method does not take any input parameters and is useful for formatting text, standardizing input, and ensuring case-insensitive comparisons.

**Syntax:**

```java
String lowerString = originalString.toLowerCase();
```

---

**Example:**

```java
class Seedit {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Declare and initialize a string
        String message = "HELLO WORLD";

        // Convert the string to lowercase
        String lowerMessage = message.toLowerCase();

        // Print the result
        System.out.println("Lowercase Message: " + lowerMessage);
    }
}
```

**Expected Output:**

```default
Lowercase Message: hello world
```

